Package: UMI4Cats
Title: UMI4Cats: Processing, analysis and visualization of UMI-4C chromatin contact data
Version: 0.99.4
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Mireia",
           family = "Ramos-Rodriguez",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "mireiarr9@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8083-2445")),
    person(given = "Marc",
           family = "Subirana-Granes",
           role = c("aut"),
           email = "msubirana@igtp.cat"))
URL: https://github.com/Pasquali-lab/UMI4Cats
Description: UMI-4C is a technique that allows characterization of 3D chromatin contacts with a bait of interest. This package allows processing of UMI-4C data, starting with FASTQ files and finishing with statistical tests to call differential contacts in two conditions.
BugReports: https://github.com/Pasquali-lab/UMI4Cats/issues
